      • enumerateWorldNames

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> enumerateWorldNames()
        Provides a List of world-names which this provider supports providing. Only the first element in the List object may be null. If the first returned element is null, then it indicates that the list that follows is not exhaustive. If this provider does not support enumeration, this method returns null. TODO: This should be on a wiki. Case 1: Supports full enumeration (All Worlds enumerable) Returns non-null, no elements are null. Case 2: Supports partial enumeration (Some World enumerable) Returns non-null, 1st element null, the rest not-null. Case 3: Enumeration not supported Returns null.
